   Qualifications - A Timeline Of My Journey

2010-2013
Kindergarten

Graduated from St James Kindergarten in Grey Lynn, Singapore in 2013 after 3 years of kindergarten.

2014-2017
Primary School

Received an academic curriculum distinction award at the prizegiving for his primary school in 2017 (year 6), graduated from Point View School in Auckland, New Zealand in 2017 after spending three years in New Zealand after previously moving from Singapore.

2018-2019
Intermediate

Received Science Cup in the first year of intermediate (year 7) in the school's 2018 prizegiving, graduated from Somerville Intermediate School in Auckland, New Zealand in year 8 after two years in intermediate as well as winning the Science cup again in the school's 2018 prizegiving, along with a class academic distinction award.

2020-2024
College/High School

Recevied numerous awards in first high school prizegiving in 2020, including an excellence award and other awards. Participated in several competitions such as the Epro8 Engineering Challenge in which his team won for the Auckland region out of all year 9's and 10's. Passed all NCEA levels and graduated from Botany Downs Secondary College in 2024 in year 13.

2025-2030
University

Received Science Cup in the first year of intermediate (year 7) in the school's 2018 prizegiving, graduated from Somerville Intermediate School in Auckland, New Zealand in year 8 after two years in intermediate as well as winning the Science cup again in the school's 2018 prizegiving, along with a class academic distinction award.
